law.catch_line: Inclusion of osteopaths within references to physicians in executive orders.
law.text: Any reference in an executive order to "medical doctor," "M.D.," or "physician" shall be deemed to include a doctor of osteopathy or D.O., unless either of those terms is specifically excluded.
law.history: Created 2000 Ky. Acts ch. 413, sec. 1, effective July 14, 2000.
